The paper deals with image editing applications and proposes a modification to alpha matting networks using deep learning approaches. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves studying variations of the training regime and exploring a wide range of existing and novel loss functions, which could fall under the Graphics (cs.GR) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The use of deep learning approaches also suggests that the paper could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves predicting foreground and background colours, which could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
